This paper deals with attribute prediction in images, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a structured inference approach using deep neural networks, which involves learning potential functions and applying the sum-product algorithm. This suggests that the paper may also fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions using the CelebA dataset, which is commonly used for facial attribute analysis (cs.CL). Finally, the paper also discusses the potential for uncovering hidden relationships between attributes, which could be relevant to the field of cryptography (cs.CR).
